<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0B386FFF4DFDA9FE1AFD40" box="[136,479,614,641]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFF4DFDA9FE1AFD40" blockId="602.[136,479,614,641]" box="[136,479,614,641]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<heading id="D09A81B1ED0B386FFF4DFDA9FE1AFD40" bold="true" box="[136,479,614,641]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF4DFDA9FE1AFD40" bold="true" box="[136,479,614,641]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFF1AFDA8FE1AFD40" authority="Illg, 1958" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[223,479,614,641]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF1AFDA8FEA6FD40" bold="true" box="[223,355,614,641]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0B386FFEAEFDA9FE1AFD40" author="Illg" box="[363,479,615,641]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0B386FFF4DFD65FD55F9D6" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFF4DFD65FD55F9D6" blockId="602.[136,778,683,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF4DFD65FF3EFD04" bold="true" box="[136,251,683,709]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body vermiform, elongate, cylindrical, usually curved or coiled, consisting of prosome incorporating all pedigerous somites and small abdomen. Cephalosome expanded laterally, but fused with or obscurely defined from metasome. Swimming legs confined to anterior part of prosome, separated from one another by regular intervals. Fourth pedigerous somite much longerthan remainingpartofbody, formingbroodpouchincorporating fifth pedigerous somite. Genital openings located posteriorly on prosome. Abdomen 1-segmented, small, incompletely articulated from prosome. Caudal rami distinct, armed with 6 small setae. Rostrum as anterior prominence on cephalosome. Antennule unsegmented, consistingof extremely expanded, globular proximal part and narrow distal part; armed with several setae on both parts. Antenna 2- or 3-segmented; terminal segment (endopod) terminating in claw, with few setae. Labrum obscure, notcovering mouthparts. Mandible and maxillule lobate, bearing several setae. Maxilla unsegmented or incompletely 2-segmented, with 3 or 4 setae. Maxilliped absent. Legs 1–4 broad, biramous, each with 1- or 2- segmented protopod. Basis with outer seta in all legs; basis of leg 1 lacking innerdistal element. Exopods 1- or 2-segmented; endopods unsegmented. Setaeon rami mostly short, broad, spiniform, with nipple-like tip. Leg 4 with or without inner coxal seta. Leg 5 absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0B386FFF78F9EEFE1FF99A" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFF78F9EEFE1FF99A" blockId="602.[136,778,683,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF78F9EEFE9CF9F8" bold="true" box="[189,345,1567,1594]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED0B386FFF78F9EEFF3DF9FB" box="[189,248,1568,1594]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFEB5F9D1FF0FF99D" authority="(Henderson, 1930)" baseAuthorityName="Henderson" baseAuthorityYear="1930" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFEB5F9D1FDB4F9F8" box="[368,625,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes huntsmani</emphasis>
(Henderson, 1930)
</taxonomicName>
by original designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED0B386FFF78F9AAFC99FE52" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFF78F9AAFD5EF835" blockId="602.[136,778,683,2070]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF78F9AAFEEFF9BF" bold="true" box="[189,298,1636,1662]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0B386FFE89F9ADFE1CF9BF" author="Illg" box="[332,473,1635,1662]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" pagination="463 - 649" part="107" refId="ref328917" refString="Illg, P. L. (1958) North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 107 (3390), 463 - 649. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.108 - 3390.463" title="North American copepods of the family Notodelphyidae" type="journal article" year="1958">Illg (1958)</bibRefCitation>
established the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFF4DF94BFEC1F95E" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[136,260,1669,1695]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF4DF94BFEC1F95E" box="[136,260,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFE1AF94BFE8AF903" authority="Henderson, 1931" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="1931" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecimorpha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huntsmani">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFE1AF94BFCCFF95E" box="[479,778,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecimorpha huntsmani</emphasis>
Henderson, 1931
</taxonomicName>
and redescribed this species on the basis of newly collected specimens associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFD00F907FE4AF8C4" authority="Stimpson, 1864" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1864" class="Ascidiacea" family="Styelidae" genus="Styela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gibbsii">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFD00F907FF11F8C4" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Styela gibbsii</emphasis>
Stimpson, 1864
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED0B386FFE00F922FE30F8C7" box="[453,501,1772,1798]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">type</typeStatus>
host, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFDAFF922FE8FF8E9" authority="(Stimpson, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1864" class="Ascidiacea" family="Pyuridae" genus="Pyura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hauster">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFDAFF922FCCFF8C4" box="[618,778,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Pyura hauster</emphasis>
(Stimpson, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
from Washington, near the 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED0B386FFDBAF8C0FD6AF8E9" box="[639,687,1806,1832]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingRegion id="49A9F83FED0B386FFF6EF8FEFEB3F88B" box="[171,374,1840,1866]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DED0B386FFE4DF8FEFE25F88B" box="[392,480,1840,1866]" name="Canada" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Canada</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0B386FFE35F8FEFD5FF88B" author="Dudley, P. L." bookContentInfo="282 pp." box="[496,666,1839,1866]" journalOrPublisher="University of Washington Press, Seattle and London" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" refId="ref327924" refString="Dudley, P. L. (1966) Development and Systematics of Some Pacific Marine Symbiotic Copepods. A Study of the Biology of the Notodelphyidae, associates of Ascidians. University of Washington Press, Seattle and London, 282 pp." title="Development and Systematics of Some Pacific Marine Symbiotic Copepods. A Study of the Biology of the Notodelphyidae, associates of Ascidians" type="book" year="1966">Dudley (1966)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFF4DF89CFDEEF8AD" authority="(Stimpson, 1864)" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[136,555,1873,1900]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Pyuridae" genus="Boltenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF4DF89CFE83F8AD" box="[136,326,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Boltenia villosa</emphasis>
(Stimpson, 1864)
</taxonomicName>
as an additional host of this copepod, also from Washington State. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED0B386FFD26F8BAFF24F870" author="Illg, P. L." journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" pagination="69 - 74" part="18" refId="ref329022" refString="Illg, P. L. (1970 b) Occurrence in Sagami Bay, Japan, of Scolecodes, a remarkable copepod parasite of ascidians. Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory, 18, 69 - 74. https: // doi. org / 10.5134 / 175627" title="Occurrence in Sagami Bay, Japan, of Scolecodes, a remarkable copepod parasite of ascidians" type="journal article" year="1970">Illg (1970b)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the discovery of this species associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFF0DF876FD6EF812" authority="(Hartmeyer, 1906)" baseAuthorityName="Hartmeyer" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[200,683,1976,2003]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Styelidae" genus="Cnemidocarpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fertilis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF0DF876FE03F813" box="[200,454,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Cnemidocarpa fertilis</emphasis>
(Hartmeyer, 1906)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFD35F876FE79F835" authority="(Kiaer, 1893)" baseAuthorityName="Kiaer" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Ascidiacea" family="Styelidae" genus="Cnemidocarpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="finmarkiensis">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFD35F876FCC6F813" box="[752,771,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFF4DF814FEDAF835" box="[136,287,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">finmarkiensis</emphasis>
(Kiaer, 1893)
</taxonomicName>
in Japanese waters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED0B386FFF78F832FC99FE52" blockId="602.[136,778,683,2070]" lastBlockId="602.[810,1452,173,403]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFE8BF832FE0FF7D7" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[334,458,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFE8BF832FE0FF7D7" box="[334,458,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFCEFFF63FC15FF06" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[810,976,173,199]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFCEFFF63FC15FF06" box="[810,976,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Campodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0B386FFC10FF63FBFEFF06" box="[981,1083,173,199]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFC10FF63FBF3FF06" bold="true" box="[981,1078,173,199]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, especiallyinleg form. However, comparedto 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFC7BFF01FBA1FF28" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[958,1124,207,233]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campodelphys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFC7BFF01FBA1FF28" box="[958,1124,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Campodelphys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4ED0B386FFBA9FF01FB12FF28" box="[1132,1239,207,233]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFBA9FF01FB14FF28" bold="true" box="[1132,1233,207,233]" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">gen. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFAC0FF01FA44FF28" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[1285,1409,207,233]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFAC0FF01FA44FF28" box="[1285,1409,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the body is more elongate, the prosome isexpanded to include all the pedigerous somites plus the genital somite, and the free abdomen is unsegmented. In addition, the maxilliped is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED0B386FFC68FE99FBECFEB0" authorityName="Illg" authorityYear="1958" box="[941,1065,343,369]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Scolecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="602" pageNumber="603" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED0B386FFC68FE99FBECFEB0" box="[941,1065,343,369]" italics="true" pageId="602" pageNumber="603">Scolecodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but present in 
